Title : [A case of congenital multiple arthrogryposis. Considerations].
Date : 1990
Publication_type : Journal Article
Abstract : The paper describes the diagnosis, clinical, anatomopathological and etiopathogenetic aspects of a case of congenital multiple arthrogryposis. The importance of the dialogue between the obstetrician and the parents is underlined in terms of the latters' psychological preparation. The obstetrician must also prepare for an atraumatic delivery, in addition to planning the treatment protocol for the neonate.
